{"/service/ndnp/in/batch_in_janeway_ver01/data/sn87055779/00416150886/1930102901/0319.xml":{"full_text":"ACT TO DEFEAT!\nLABOR PARTY IS\nSEEN INJ.ONDON\nConservatives to Strike at\nUnemployment Issue in\nParliament.\nBy KEITH JONES\nUnited Press Staff Correspondent\nLONDON, Aug. 28.\u2014The shadow ox\nan early and well organized attempt\nby the Conservative party to defeat\nthe Labor government hung over\npolitical London on the eve of the\nopening of parliament Tuesday.\nThe conservative attack waa ex\npected to take the form of an amend\nment to the section of the king\u2019s\nspeech relating to unemployment. To\nthis section the conservatives have\nIndicated they will seek to add an\namendment reading that parliament\n\u201chumbly regrets the failure of the\ngovernment to reduce the evil of un\nemployment.\u201d\nThis amendment may be reached\nas early as Monday, Nov. 3, and the\nquestion whether the conservatives\nwill be able to swing the support of\nthe Liberal party to the amendment\nis regarded as vital to the future of\nthe MacDonald cabinet.\nUnemployment Great\nThe precarious position of the La\nbor government\u2014in office since June\nof 1929\u2014is Indicated by an analysis\nof the r.resent position of the parties.\nThere are 287 Labor members; and\nthe opposition may muster 269 Con\nservatives, 68 Liberals, five Indepen\ndents and two Irish Nationalists\u2014a\ntotal of 324 and, what is more im\nportant, a majority of 37 over the\ngovernment.\nThe government\u2019s hope lies in Its\nability to prove to the majority of the\nHouse of Commons that the present\nunemployment situation, with 2,\n000,000 out of work in Britain, is due\nto World-Wide causes outside the\nprovince of the labor or any other\ngovernment to control.\nA heavy legislative program Is on\nthe schedule for the new session of\nparliament. The- projects include an\nunemployment Insurance bill, a fac\ntory bill, a bill to ratify the Washing\nton 8-hour convention, a consumers\u2019\ncouncil bill, a land valuation bill, an\neducation bill to raise the compulsory\nschool age to 15, and a town-plan\nning bill.\nSituation Grows Worse\nSome of these bills, such as the\nfactory bill, the consumers\u2019 bill, and\nthe education bill, were scheduled for\nconsideration at the last session. They\nhad to be dropped, however, owing to\nthe prolonged debates over the coal\nbill, the finance bill and unemploy\nment.\nThe figure of unemployed today Is\nnearly doube that when the Labor\ngovernment took office on a platform\nwhich promised a radical improve\nment of the unemployment situation.\nThe claim by labor men that the\npresent situation probably would be\nas bad, or even worse, under any ad\nministration has not given the party\nleaders any considerable peace of\nt mind, and they are preparing for a\nbattle which may result in defeat And\nAn early general election.\nRUBBER FROM OIL.\nWASHINGTON. Artificial rubber\nmay yet be produced if the experi\nments of the United States bureau\nof standards prove of commercial\nvalue. This office has produced crys\ntalline rubber from crude petroleum\nby the extraction of certain hydro\ncarbons from it, according to Dr.\nGeorge Burgess, director of the bu\nrtau. \u201cSolid rubber is an almost cer\ntainty If the work can be extended,\u201d\nhe says.\nBor whoever meditates a crime U\nguilty of the deed. \u2014Juvenal.\nm\nMODISH M1TZ1 Mitzi Coats Come Out On Top \u2014By Jay V. Jay\nJUL\nJl_i\nintd bu turned philanthropist An appeal for\nclothes from the needy has gone straight to her heart\nShe\u2019s going to be very systematic about her assistance\nto the cause and find oat what is needed. She has\ndressed for \u201cresearch work\u201d in her very smart and\nvery warm earners hair coat with the fitted coach\nman\u2019s design. Doable breasted and with wide revere.\n\nPolly, in her new tweed coat with the shaggy rac\ncoon collar, is adding her last year\u2019s coats to Mitzi\u2019s\nso that their gifts to charity are going to necessitate\na truck. Notice that Polly\u2019s coat has a narrow belt,\nslash pockets and there\u2019s quite a flare to the silhou\nette. This is a popular campus coat in most colleges\ntoo.\n\u2014Tfllfgl Q *mx QQBv\u00a3 ill\nWarm things are very much needed, and Mitd\nthinks of her old coats and decides that the only\nthing to do is to cut down her wardrobe. In doing\nit, she will have to buy this very new Russian tunic\ncoat in order not to freeze herself. She might get\nher dressmaker to make up a lot of these coats be\ncause one really feels more comfortable in smart\nthings.\nAdelaide brought a donation of last year's suit and\ncoat for the poor. Because she bought one of the new\nfour piece costumes which includea a three piece suit\nand a top coat to match. It solves all the coat prob\nlems as to matching dresses or blouses. Polly thinks\nshe is \u201cneedy\u201d enough to wear Adelaide\u2019s hwt year\u2019s\nclothes. Who isn\u2019t poor in one sense or another?\nGrand Rapids Churches Act\nTo Aid City's Unemployed\nBy United Frees:\nGRAND RAPIDS, Mich., Oct. 28.\u2014\nChurches of this city, considering the\nbusiness Repression and unemploy\nment a matter which may be relieved\nthrough joint application of prayer\nand lay consideration, Monday were\nembarked on a week of special prayer.\nIn most of the churches of the city\nministers Sunday devoted one of their\nservices to a discussion of present day\nbusiness conditions, and a return of\nprosperity. In some, mass meetings,\nattended by, state and city officials,\nwere held.\nMost of the ministers, however,\nwent on the premise that while the\npresent depression can be considered\nan act of God, it cannot be looked\nupon as a divine visitation, such as a\npiague.\n\u201cThe lack of prosperity today,\u201d Dr.\nRalph J. White, of the Trinity Meth\nodist Episcopal church, said, \u201cmay be\ncalled the result of a violation by\nman of God\u2019s laws, and the country\nmay be suffering punishment fo# for\ngetting, in times of prosperity, the\nteachings of God.\u201d\nThe reason for the fall of Carthage,\ngiven by H. G. Wells, the historian,\nas money, may be applied to the pres\nent predicament of business, Dr.\nWhite said.\nAt the Central Reformed church it\nwas announced that a $60,000 build\ning project would be started at once\nalthough funds for the work are not\nentirely subscribed. The Rev. John A.\nDykstra, pastor, explained the work\nwill be started In order to give em\nployment.\nDuring this week the Ministers' as\nsociation will continue to bring the\nmatter of needed prosperity before\ntheir followers, particularly at mid\nweek services, and they also will con\nsider ways and means of providihg\nimmediate employment for those fac\ning a winter of want and hardship.\nMEXICAN OPERATOR\nGETS RADIO PERMIT\nBy rnited Fresg:\nVERA CRUZ, Mex., Oct. 28.\u2014Tiie\ndepartment of public works has\ngranted permission to Manuel Angel\nFernandez, of this city, for installa\ntion of a powerful radio broadcast\ning station. The new station, to be\nused for commercial- broadcasts, will\nhave a 500 watt transmitter, operat\ning on a wave length of 1,120 kilo\ncycles. The call letters will be\nXETF.\na\nw.\nYou\u2019ll go a\nlong way to\nequal these\nvalues\nKeep Smiling\nwith -Kellys\n29 x 4.40\n29 x 430\n30x430\n28 x 4.75\n29 x 5.00\n31 x 5.25\n29 x 530\nnuet\n.6 5.55\n6.20\n6.30\n7.40\n7.95\n9.75\n9.95\n32 x 6.00\n12.90\nLotta Miles\nOtbar situ proportionately low\nLIBERAL\nALLOWANCE\non your old dres\ntoward a set of\nKELLY REGISTERED\nBALLOONS\ntires are strong and tough, the way Kelly\nbuilds all its tires.\nThey have a wide, thick tread of pure\nrubber. They\u2019re not only good looking\u2014\nthey are good. Extra strength and service\nhave been built into them at every point.\nKelly Lotta Miles tires are thebest tires\never offered to the public at anywhere\nnear these low prices. They are guaran\nteed for life.\nTHOMAS RUBBER CO.\n212 Lincoln way East\nHL E. WiOette, Mgr. Phone 3-2354\nDependable service for 23 years to the motoring public.\nAll KELLY dealers are Independent dealers\nThree-Minute\nJourneys\nTHE TOMB OF KINO TOT\nOf all the magnificent tombs In\nthe Valley o the Kings that of\nTut-ankh-Amen is the smallest and\nleast pretentious, yet it was the\nrichest in treasures when the ex\ncavations under the direction of the\nEarl of Carnarvon and Howard Car\nter unearthed it.\nIn case you do not remember the\nhistory of this Pharaoh\u2014although in\nthe past few years much has been\nwritten about him\u2014you must know\nthat his Teign was very short. This\nprobably accounts for the appearance\nthe tomb gives of having been hastily\nconstructed and the helter-skelter\nmanner inr which the contents were\ndisposed.\nThe death chamber of the king is\nnow open to visitors and should not\nbe neglected by any traveler to the\nNile valley. It was here that the\nmummy of the young Pharaoh was\nfound in a giant sarcophagus, clad in\ngolden robes of untold value. In the\nouter chamber stands one of the first\ncandle holders of its kind used In\nEgypt. It was this appliance with its\ntwisted wick which gave an inkling of\nthe system of lighting the places oc\ncupied by the/Egyptian kings more\nthan three thousand years ago.\nOff in a corner the searchers found\nfour magnificent chariots with golden\nwheels dismounted so as to permit\nthe vehicles to >e taken into the\ntomb.\nKing Tut-ankh-Amen belonged to\nthe family of Akhnaton, the Pharaoh\nwhom H. O. Wells called \u201cthe first\nindividual in history\u201d. King Tut was\nthe successor to Aknaton, who has\nbeen called also the first pacifist be\ncause he turned a deaf ear to the\npleas of his people for aid against at\ntacking enemies. But King Tut was\nnot the direct successor. There was\nan interval very short, during which\nSmenkhkara reigned briefly and upon\nhis death Tut-ankh-Amen came to\nthe throne. Originally his name was\nTut-ankh-Aton but he changed it\nwhen he restored the Amen worship\nwhic Akhnaton had abolished and at\nthe same time moved the capitol back\nto Thebes from Luxor.\nTut-ankh-Amen never was a bril\nliant figure in history and had it not\nbeen for the fact that the discovery\nof his tomb unearthed such vast\ntreasure and at the same time\nbrought to light papyrus records\nwhich bridged a gap in history, the\nworld today probably would be none\nthe wiser for his having lived.\nAs it is, however, travelers with\nthe price of the trip have beeaten a\npath to his tomb and from a virtual\nnonentity Tut-ankh-Amen has be\ncome one of the most widely known\nHOOSIER DROPS DEAD\nDURING CONVENTION\nBy United Preagt\nPRINCETON, Ind., Oct. 28.\u2014James\nM. Scantlin, 88, former hardware\ndealer at Princeton ,and Civil war\nveteran, dropped dead Monday at\nthe Hotel Kidd.\nScantlin resided at LaGrange, Ind.,\nwith his only child, Mrs. H. R.\nClark. He was attending a G. A. R.\nconvention In Princeton.\nKEEP COOL IN AIDING HURT\nPERSON.\nQuite frequently we are forced to\ntake care of someone who has met\nwith an accident and is bleeding. No\none of us enjoys this experience and\nIf the choice of going for the doctor\nor staying with the bleeder is given,\nI know what most of us would rather\ndo.\nThe injured person is usually just\nas timid and frightened as you are at\nthe sight of blood. He is bleeding\nand the doctor has been called.\nEverybody is distressed and worried.\nWhat shall we do until the medico\ncomes?\nWe are frightened for fear the\npatient will bleed to death before the j\ndoctor arrives. The friends get ex- j\ncited and almost always the patient\ngets excited. The more you get ex- j\ncited, the more he does.\n\u201cFirst Keep CooP*\nHow well I recall a scene in medical\ncollege many years ago. The profes\nsor was asking his students as to the\nproper first procedure in a case of\nbleeding. Many excellent and correct\noutlines of the procedure as recited\nin the text books were given by the\nanxious-to-please students.\n\u201cNo, no,\u201d stormed the professor,\nand to the amazement of all stated,\n\u201cThe proper care is first to keep cool.\nAfter that,\" he said, \u201cstop the bleed-!\ning.\u201d\nIf we would always remember this\nand act upon It, there would be less\nexcitement whenever such emergen\ncies arise. A life may be saved in\nconsequence.\nVarious methods of stopping the\nblood artificially have been described1\nby the surgeons. 'Which one to use\ndepends on the type and site of the\nbleeding.\nAs a rule, bleeding will stop In a\nfew minutes anyhow, if the patient is\nkept quiet. The firm pressure of a\ndressing may do the trick. Such a\ndressing soaked in very hot water will\noften stop the bleeding.\nIf the bleeding continues and you\nare doubtful as to the vessel that is\nresponsible, something else must be\ndone. Then a \u201ctourniquet\u201d must be\napplied.\nApply a Tourniquet\nA tourniquet is simply a constrict\ning band placed around the Injured\nlimb between the wound and the\nheart. This pressure shuts off the\nflow of Wood to this part of the\nbody. It consists of a pad, which\nserves as the pressure part, and a\nband. The pad may be made of a\nsmall stone, a piece of wood, or\nother hard object, wrapped in some\nmaterial to make it less rough. j\nIf sufficient pressure cannot be j\nexerted by hand, it may easily be\naided by placing a stick under the\nbinder and twisting. But you must\nbe careful not to exert sufficient\npressure to cause discoloration or\nmarked pain. Always have a physi\ncian Inspect your work and finish the\njob.\nRemember you are only treating\nthe injured person until the doctor\narrives. If no one has come within\nthe hour, and the tourniquet is on,\nrelease it. Allow the tourniquet to\nremain loose but in place. If the\nbleeding appears again it may be\ntightened.\nIf the tourniquet is left on a\nwound too long death of the nearby\ntissue will take place, due to tutting\noff the blood supply. This Is a serious\nmatter and its danger should always\nbe borne in mind.\nAnd don\u2019t forget to keep cool!\nSAVINGS DEPOSITORS\nIN PERU ARE PAID\nBy United Freed\nLIMA, Peru, Oct. 28.\u2014Payment of\nthe accounts of 59,000 savings de\npositors of the bank of Peru and Lon\ndon was started Monday morning\nwhen the bank reopened after being\nclosed for two weeks. A loan of $1,\n980,000 from other Lima banks made\nthe payments possible. Heavy with\ndrawals, which endangered the bank,\nwere responsible for its closing. Pay\nments Monday to Individual depos\nitors were limited to $1,650 each.\nGOTHAM GANG CZAR\nREPORTED BETTER\nBy International New* Seerie*;\nNEW YORK. Oct. 28.\u2014Jack Tegs\u201d\nDiamond, racketeer who was shot two\nweeks ago by gunmen In his hotel,\ncontinued to Improve Monday. He\nwill leave Metropolitan hospital on\nWelfare Prison Island within a week\nor 10 days If his Improvement con\ntinues, hospital officials said. No\ncharge is pending against him.\nSTOMACH UPSET\nGet at the real cause. That\u2019s what\nthousands of stomach sufferers are\ndoing now. Instead of taking tonics,\nor trying to patch up h poor indiges\ntion, they are attacking the real\ncause of the aliment\u2014clogged liver\nand disordered bowels.\nDr. Edwards Olive Tablets help\narouse the liver In a soothing, healing\nway. When the liver and bowels are\nperforming their natural functions,\npeople rarely suffer from Indigestion\nand stomach troubles.\nHave you a bad taste, coated\ntongue, poor appetite, a lazy, don\u2019t\ncare feeling, no ambition or energy\ntrouble with undigested foods? Try\nOlive Tablets, the substitute for calo\nmel.\nDr. Edwards Olive Tablets are a\npurely vegetable compound. Know\nthem by their olive color. They do\nthe work without griping, cramps or\npain. All druggists. 15c, 30c and 60c.\nTake one or two at bedtime for\nquick relief. Eat what you like.\u2014Adv\nFolks You Don\u2019t Need Cash\nClip This Coupon!\nGood for Three\nDollars and Your\nDown Payment\non